      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed on the pedicle screw shank and rod interface regions. Grid Convergence Index for stiffness QoI was 1.4%; yield force GCI was 2.1%. Final mesh selected at intermediate refinement level balancing accuracy and runtime. Discretization error is within acceptable bounds per project requirements."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 1,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative solver residuals converge to machine-precision tolerances; energy balance error <0.1%.",
      "rationale": "Nonlinear Newton-Raphson solver residuals converged to 1e-6 relative tolerance for all load steps. Energy imbalance across all increments was below 0.05%. Default Ansys sparse direct solver used for linear subproblems; no iterative solver divergence observed."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Independent peer review of model setup, boundary conditions, and post-processing scripts confirms no operator-induced errors.",
      "rationale": "A second analyst independently reconstructed boundary conditions and load application from the ASTM F1717 protocol and compared against the primary analyst's setup. No discrepancies were found. Post-processing scripts for QoI extraction were reviewed and validated against manual spot-checks. Use error is considered controlled per project requirements."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Constitutive model (bilinear isotropic hardening for Ti-6Al-4V) validated against coupon tensile data; contact formulation verified against known interface behavior.",
      "rationale": "Bilinear isotropic hardening parameters were fit to manufacturer-supplied Ti-6Al-4V tensile coupon data (n=5 coupons). Augmented Lagrangian contact with friction coefficient μ=0.2 was selected based on literature and sensitivity analysis. Model form uncertainty was propagated through the QoI comparison and found to contribute less than 3% to total model uncertainty, consistent with Gradation 3 requirements."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Material properties and geometric parameters derived from traceable measurements; uncertainty in inputs propagated to QoI uncertainty.",
      "rationale": "Elastic modulus (114 GPa), yield strength (880 MPa), and ultimate tensile strength (950 MPa) sourced from certificate of conformance for each lot. Screw geometry digitized from CMM measurements (tolerance ±0.01 mm). Latin hypercube sampling (n=200) used to propagate input uncertainty to QoI; 95th-percentile QoI uncertainty was 4.2%, within the 10% acceptance bound."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "N≥10 test specimens from production lots; dimensional and material traceability documented.",
      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs tested across two independent laboratories. All screws sourced from the same production lot with documented dimensional inspection. Inter-laboratory coefficient of variation for stiffness was 4.1%, confirming reproducibility. Sample size satisfies Gradation 3 requirements per project requirements documentation."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Multiple test conditions (load rates, environmental conditions) explored to characterize model sensitivity.",
      "rationale": "Testing was conducted at a single quasi-static load rate (5 mm/min) per ASTM F1717 protocol. No variation in environmental conditions or load rate was explored. This limits the test conditions factor to Gradation 2, one level below the required Gradation 3. This gap is acknowledged and accepted given the deterministic quasi-static nature of the COU and the conservative acceptance bounds applied."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA inputs (geometry, material, boundary conditions) demonstrably equivalent to experimental specimen parameters within stated tolerances.",
      "rationale": "Experimental specimen dimensions were measured post-test and compared to FEA geometry; mean dimensional deviation was 0.03 mm (0.4%). Material certificates confirmed lot-to-lot consistency. Boundary conditions replicated ASTM F1717 fixture geometry including vertebral body block spacing of 100 mm. Equivalency is confirmed at Gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoI differences <10% and E/uval < 1.96 for all three QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm).",
      "rationale": "Stiffness: FEA 312 N/mm vs. experimental mean 308 N/mm (1.3% difference; E/uval=0.41). Yield force: FEA 1842 N vs. experimental mean 1809 N (1.8% difference; E/uval=0.62). Force at 40 mm: FEA 2104 N vs. experimental mean 2071 N (1.6% difference; E/uval=0.54). All three QoIs satisfy both acceptance criteria at Gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are directly mechanistically linked to clinical failure modes of pedicle screw constructs.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness governs load sharing with the biological tissue; yield force is the threshold for permanent deformation leading to loss of fixation; force at 40 mm displacement characterizes post-yield energy absorption relevant to fatigue initiation. All three QoIs are standard ASTM F1717 outputs and are cited in FDA guidance as relevant to spinal implant performance. Relevance is established at Gradation 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities replicate COU loading mode, device geometry, and regulatory context (ASTM F1717 static compression-bending).",
      "rationale": "The validation activity is identical in loading mode (ASTM F1717 static compression-bending), device geometry (non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw), material (Ti-6Al-4V), and regulatory context (Class II 510(k) submission) to the COU. No extrapolation in loading mode or geometry is required. Relevance is rated Gradation 3."
    }
